  "prompt": "What are the change theories?",
  "response": "There are several change theories in organizational and personal development. Here are some of the most prominent ones:\n\n1. Lewin's Change Management Model\n- Unfreeze\n- Change\n- Refreeze\n\n2. Kotter's 8-Step Change Model\n- Create urgency\n- Form a powerful coalition\n- Create a vision for change\n- Communicate the vision\n- Remove obstacles\n- Create short-term wins\n- Build on the change\n- Anchor the changes\n\n3. Bridges' Transition Model\n- Ending, Losing, Letting Go\n- Neutral Zone\n- New Beginning\n\n4. ADKAR Change Management Model\n- Awareness\n- Desire\n- Knowledge\n- Ability\n- Reinforcement\n\n5. Kubler-Ross Change Curve\n- Shock\n- Denial\n- Frustration\n- Depression\n- Experiment\n- Decision\n- Integration\n\n6. Prosci Change Management Methodology\n- Preparing for change\n- Managing change\n- Reinforcing change\n\n7. Action Research Model\n- Diagnosing\n- Planning\n- Taking action\n- Evaluating\n- Specifying learning\n\nEach theory offers unique perspectives and strategies for managing organizational and personal change.",
